The paper discusses the use of machine learning for cyber security, specifically for botnet detection from network traffic data. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also provides guidelines and recommendations for using supervised machine learning, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of network traffic data implies a focus on network and internet architecture (cs.NI), and the consideration of attack characteristics suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SI).
